ANNOUNCEMENT: We are incredibly excited and honored to be back at @peabodyessex this June as a part of their Pride programming.  This year’s theme will be inspired by Midsummer festivals, as well as a handful of other favorites of ours that tie into the celebration.  The night will bring back the incredible @msanamatronic, who will be spinning the best tracks for maypole dancing 😉 and @dbdfloralboutique & @burialground back on the stunning florals.  The party will kick off with a pre-show talk with @pslinks about our process and inspiration behind the night.  Please join us on Friday June 23rd (details to follow) at The Peabody Essex Museum for the opening party.  The installation will be up for a few days afterwards so if you can’t make it, or if you want to see it again, you will have a few more opportunities!  As always, thank you to @danielle.0lsen for spearheading and including us in these events.  Hope to see you there! 🌸 (swipe through for some photos from last October’s “Alchemical” event, taken by @chezphoto)

I’m doing another ✨Virtual Create Night✨ with the @peabodyessex! This time around, I’ll be teaching you how to make paper flowers (materials provided!) and again, this is over ZOOOOM so you do not have to be anywhere except in front of your computer/phone/ipad whatevs. I am totally unqualified and a little annoying but I love doing it. So please come and have a drink with me and make a goddamn flower ok? (The Create Night takes place on June 15th at 7pm est and you can find tickets in my bio) Actually, the same paper flowers can be seen on some of the new masks at the exhibition @hoganmclaughlin and I are presenting on June 23rd at the museum for their Midsummer Pride dance party! Details about that below:
.
If you are in the Salem, MA area and want to get nasty I am telling you not to miss the Midsummer exhibition/ party. Hogan is working on a new collection inspired by the Scandinavian festival while I created 7 new masks to accompany his pieces that draw inspo from folklore, a Midsummer Night’s Dream, and my favorite creatures that come out in the warmer months. If you’re unfamiliar with our previous event, you can find images of our last exhibition on both of our Instagram pins. Not only will we be graced with @msanamatronic again in the dj BoOth, @dbdfloralboutique & @burialground leading florals, butttt there will be a special Midsummer @light_witch Photo Booth. Courtney will be bringing all of the mystical summer festival energy with her portrait photography and it will make for a special keepsake for all of u bbs who turn looks and want them documented by a legend. Special cocktails and light bites inspired by the festival will be servedddd.💕💋 tickets to this are also in my bio! Can’t wait to padam padam with u 🔥

SENSITIVE CONTENT: It was a dream come true to transform into Peacock Eros and be photographed by my favorite, @pauloctavious for issue 3 of @sensitivecontentmag. I am v honored to be in this issue alongside all of these inspiring people. Thank you so much for having me, @happydevilboy. You can purchase a copy via the link in my linktree #heavingbush 💋❤️
Caption this

Last night was such a joyful one at the @peabodyessex!  We want to extend our heartfelt gratitude to everyone that made this event possible (again!). It’s a privilege to be able to show our work in such an incredible setting, and to be able to tie in an insane Pride dance party with the incredible @msanamatronic at the helm is the cherry on top.  Today we moved our entire installation into a pop up gallery so if you couldn’t make it last night, our work will be up through Monday ✨

Thank you to the entire Education team at PEM, headed by @danielle.0lsen with @lilliangendreau @caitlyn_buja, for always having a handle on all the moving parts that go into a production like this.  Thank you to @pslinks for the most calming presence and lovely chat moderator.  Thank you to @jamiemooers @dbdfloralboutique @burialground for once again killing it with the spectacular florals.  Thank you to my team @branimirai @nanaokazakiplotkin @thecostumeshopchi for your unmatched craftsmanship and attention to detail.  Thank you to @katejones_stitchart for collaborating with me and adding a new layer of dimension to my work.  Thank you to @light_witch (with assistance from @karlozo) for curating THE best photo booth experience for the guests.  Thank you to @ryanmrray @mattwmurray @pondyriver @blackmagicmedic @zackhoag @horseauthority @phonebex Grady, and countless others for all your time and help in the last-minute adjustments and details.  Thank you to @levipreston for the always beautiful lighting.  Huge thank you to the crew at PEM for working with us to get the area exhibition-ready (and struck the next morning). And finally thank you to all our family and friends, old and new, for coming out and supporting us and celebrating Pride in such a fantastic way.  Love to you all ❤️🌈🌸

New on the Local Artist’s Wall, “This Arcana is Major” by @billsafi! ✨

“This Arcana is Major is a series of nine selections from the Major Arcana included in Bill Crisafi’s forthcoming tarot deck (release date TBD). The deck marries his two distinct styles to bring a campy, surreal, and whimsical energy to each card. The drawings you see reference stills from his favorite films using characters that frequent his work, some personal experiences as a queer person, and his connection to the witch archetype. Being a Massachusetts native and former Salem local plays a big role in Bill’s point of view as an artist. 

These fine art prints were digitally printed on USA made archival cotton rag paper with a velvet texture. Bill added gold acrylic details by hand to each of the nine pieces to reflect the light and add dimension. Bordering the works are custom arch mats. Each mat was hand-gilded by the artist using gold leaf to call back to medieval art through a 1970’s lens. The finishing touch on this series are the etched brass plaques that were made locally in Massachusetts. While prints of these images will appear in his online shop in the future, these customized pieces are one of a kind and only available at @hauswitch.” 

Email hello@hauswitch.com for pricing and availability! #hauswitch 

#billcrisafi #salem #salemma #salemmassachusetts #witchcity #salemwitch
